## Cross-Machine Sync

When completing OS-specific operations (plugin install, cron/scheduled tasks, shell scripts, `settings.local.json` edits, OS-specific tools), proactively ask the user "Sync this to your other machine?" If yes, write a task following `~/.claude/cross-machine/README.md`.

Pure config file changes (settings.json, CLAUDE.md, skills/commands/rules) sync via git directly — no task needed.
